> # [Warning]($block.attrs('warning'))
>This guide is not battle tested. Corrections and improvements from experienced 
>Neovim users are welcome.

## 1. Install Tree-Sitter parsers

These can be installed from inside neovim:

```
:TSInstall superhtml
:TSInstall supermd
:TSInstall supermd_inline
:TSInstall ziggy
:TSInstall ziggy_schema
```


## 2. Update configurations

The following snippets can be executed in a running neovim session using the
`:lua` command. Alternatively, you can place them in your init.lua to have them
run on launch.

**`nvim-lspconfig`**
```lua
vim.lsp.enable('superhtml')
vim.lsp.enable('ziggy')
vim.lsp.enable('ziggy_schema')
```

**format on save**
```lua
vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufWritePre', {
  group = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup('UserAutoFormat', {}),
  callback = function()
    if vim.lsp.buf.format ~= nil then
      vim.lsp.buf.format()
    end
  end,
})
```

**`nvim-treesitter`**
```lua
vim.filetype.add {
  extension = {
    smd = 'supermd',
    shtml = 'superhtml',
    ziggy = 'ziggy',
    ['ziggy-schema'] = 'ziggy_schema',
  },
}
```

## 3. Get all CLI tools
Get all CLI tools from the releases of each repository (or build them yourself),
make sure to make them available in `PATH`, and at that point you should be fully
setup!
